CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 5, 1945, pg. 20, reads: "The Blue Haven Restaurant at 1830 Centre Avenue, managed by Harry Stewart, opens Saturday, May 5, at 11 A. M."
TitMainTitle: Exterior of Blue Haven Restaurant with window display of portraits of Duke Ellington, Lena Horne, and possibly boxer Joe Louis, on star patterned fabric, 1830 Centre Avenue, Hill District
